results.name: a(n) is the A-sequence for the Riordan matrix R = (1/(1- x^2 - x^3), x/(1 - x^2 - x^3)) from A104578.
comment: See the comment in A319201, and the recurrence formula for A104578 from the A- and Z-sequences.
The Z-sequence for R is given by a(n+1), n >= 0.
formula: a(n) = [t^n] (1/f(t)), where f(t) = F^{[-1]}(t)/t, with the compositional inverse F^{[-1]}(t) of F(x) = 1/(1 - x^2 - x^3). The expansion of f is given in A319201.
results.author: _Wolfdieter Lang_, Oct 29 2018
